Warm welcome in our Weekly News Repository. 
First of all i'll introduce you to our SVN Repository. Actually it looks like:

* branches/
* tags/     Contain the snapshots for each edition
* trunk/    Your working directory
    en/     All stuff for the English newsletter
            Other languages can be added, if needed
     .      README, Makefiles
     logos/ This folder contains pictures)
     xml/   Contains the XML sources
     xslt/  Contains no editable content, only stylesheets
        fo/  Stylesheets for the FO output

If you want to add your Languagefolder there, just write an Email 
to: saigkill@opensuse.org.

For getting commitrights please register yourself at http://developer.berlios.de/account/register.php. 
After that, please send saigkill@opensuse.org your Accountdetails. So he can add you to the Project.

After this short introducion we go forward to explore the World.

In this Repository we have written different Documents with different goals.

TUTORIAL     - Is a Step by Step Guideline, who explains, how we can get the wished output.
DEVEL        - Contains Informations about the Process.
BUILD        - Explains how we can compile our XML/XSLT Files to get a Outputfile
TODO         - Place for Plans, Enhencements, Errors in a Stylesheet or a Layoutproblem.

